notes.text: Updated nss, nss-softokn, nss-util and nspr packages that fix several bugs and add various enhancements are now available for Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6.
notes.title: Topic

notes.text:
Network Security Services (NSS) is a set of libraries designed to support cross-platform development of security-enabled client and server applications.
Netscape Portable Runtime (NSPR) provides platform independence for non-GUI operating system facilities.

The nss, nss-softokn and nss-util packages have been upgraded to upstream versions 3.44, and the nspr packages have been upgraded to upstream version 4.21. The upgraded versions provide a number of bug fixes and enhancements over the previous versions. Notably, these upgrades allow users to upgrade to Mozilla Firefox 68 Extended Support Release. (BZ#1684609, BZ#1743623, BZ#1743625, BZ#1743628)

notes.text: In Network Security Services before 3.44, a malformed Netscape Certificate Sequence can cause NSS to crash, resulting in a denial of service.
notes.title: Vulnerability description

notes.text: nss: Handling of Netscape Certificate Sequences in CERT_DecodeCertPackage() may crash with a NULL deref leading to DoS
notes.title: Vulnerability summary

notes.text: This issue was addressed via upstream nss-3.44, which is already shipped with Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6, 7 and 8.
notes.title: Statement

notes.text: The CVSS score(s) listed for this vulnerability do not reflect the associated product's status, and are included for informational purposes to better understand the severity of this vulnerability.
